byline.original: By SHERI FINK and RICK GLADSTONE

abstract: Liberian woman is diagnosed with Ebola virus, dashing country's hope of being declared free of the disease.
lead_paragraph: Confirmation that a patient tested positive deflated hope that Liberia was now free of the Ebola virus.

headline.main: Liberia Reports First Ebola Case in Weeks
headline.print_headline: Liberia Has a New Case of Ebola
